<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<Flow xmlns="http://soap.sforce.com/2006/04/metadata">
    <apiVersion>57.0</apiVersion>
    <assignments>
        <name>Set_target_start_date</name>
        <label>Set target start date</label>
        <locationX>50</locationX>
        <locationY>695</locationY>
        <assignmentItems>
            <assignToReference>$Record.OW_target_start_date__c</assignToReference>
            <operator>Assign</operator>
            <value>
                <elementReference>$Record.ActivityDate</elementReference>
            </value>
        </assignmentItems>
    </assignments>
    <assignments>
        <description>Set the subject of the task to equal the record type name.</description>
        <name>Set_task_subject</name>
        <label>Set task subject</label>
        <locationX>50</locationX>
        <locationY>395</locationY>
        <assignmentItems>
            <assignToReference>$Record.Subject</assignToReference>
            <operator>Assign</operator>
            <value>
                <elementReference>$Record.RecordType.Name</elementReference>
            </value>
        </assignmentItems>
        <connector>
            <targetReference>Change_target_start_date</targetReference>
        </connector>
    </assignments>
    <decisions>
        <description>Move the target start date in sync with the due date.</description>
        <name>Change_target_start_date</name>
        <label>Change target start date?</label>
        <locationX>182</locationX>
        <locationY>587</locationY>
        <defaultConnectorLabel>No</defaultConnectorLabel>
        <rules>
            <name>Yes</name>
            <conditionLogic>and</conditionLogic>
            <conditions>
                <leftValueReference>$Record.ActivityDate</leftValueReference>
                <operator>IsChanged</operator>
                <rightValue>
                    <booleanValue>true</booleanValue>
                </rightValue>
            </conditions>
            <conditions>
                <leftValueReference>$Record.OW_target_start_date__c</leftValueReference>
                <operator>IsChanged</operator>
                <rightValue>
                    <booleanValue>false</booleanValue>
                </rightValue>
            </conditions>
            <connector>
                <targetReference>Set_target_start_date</targetReference>
            </connector>
            <label>Yes</label>
        </rules>
    </decisions>
    <decisions>
        <description>Checks whether the record type is one where the subject should be controlled to be the same as the record type name. There is also a legacy filter on call type here that has been copied across from a process where call type is null = true means the subject should be set. This should be removed when understood what this is controlling.</description>
        <name>Subject_update_needed</name>
        <label>Subject update needed?</label>
        <locationX>182</locationX>
        <locationY>287</locationY>
        <defaultConnector>
            <targetReference>Change_target_start_date</targetReference>
        </defaultConnector>
        <defaultConnectorLabel>Don&#39;t set subject</defaultConnectorLabel>
        <rules>
            <name>Set_subject</name>
            <conditionLogic>and</conditionLogic>
            <conditions>
                <leftValueReference>$Record.RecordType.DeveloperName</leftValueReference>
                <operator>NotEqualTo</operator>
                <rightValue>
                    <stringValue>RTTask_Task</stringValue>
                </rightValue>
            </conditions>
            <conditions>
                <leftValueReference>$Record.RecordType.DeveloperName</leftValueReference>
                <operator>NotEqualTo</operator>
                <rightValue>
                    <stringValue>Operations_request</stringValue>
                </rightValue>
            </conditions>
            <conditions>
                <leftValueReference>$Record.RecordType.DeveloperName</leftValueReference>
                <operator>NotEqualTo</operator>
                <rightValue>
                    <stringValue>OW_task</stringValue>
                </rightValue>
            </conditions>
            <conditions>
                <leftValueReference>$Record.CallType</leftValueReference>
                <operator>IsNull</operator>
                <rightValue>
                    <booleanValue>true</booleanValue>
                </rightValue>
            </conditions>
            <conditions>
                <leftValueReference>$Record.RecordType.DeveloperName</leftValueReference>
                <operator>NotEqualTo</operator>
                <rightValue>
                    <stringValue>OW_task_ad_hoc</stringValue>
                </rightValue>
            </conditions>
            <conditions>
                <leftValueReference>$Record.RecordType.DeveloperName</leftValueReference>
                <operator>NotEqualTo</operator>
                <rightValue>
                    <stringValue>BusinessDevelopment</stringValue>
                </rightValue>
            </conditions>
            <conditions>
                <leftValueReference>$Record.RecordType.DeveloperName</leftValueReference>
                <operator>NotEqualTo</operator>
                <rightValue>
                    <stringValue>CallNotes</stringValue>
                </rightValue>
            </conditions>
            <connector>
                <targetReference>Set_task_subject</targetReference>
            </connector>
            <label>Set subject</label>
        </rules>
    </decisions>
    <description>This flow will adjust the target start date as the due date moves so that tasks show correctly in list views that filter on these 2 fields. It will also auto-name legacy tasks that use a discrete record type to take the record types name. The plan is to deprecate this last component as we move away from discrete record types.</description>
    <environments>Default</environments>
    <formulas>
        <description>Returns null if there is no account linked and the account record type otherwise.</description>
        <name>account_record_type_name</name>
        <dataType>String</dataType>
        <expression>IF( 
ISBLANK( {!$Record.AccountId} ) &amp;&amp; LEFT( {!$Record.WhatId}, 3 ) &lt;&gt; &quot;001&quot;, 
&quot;&quot;, 
{!$Record.Account.RecordType.Name} 
)</expression>
    </formulas>
